        <h2>Hi, I'm Vanessa.</h2>
        <p>
          I'm a certified birth doula serving families in and around
          Kansas City. My journey into doula work began after my own transformative
          birth experience — one that showed me just how much a knowledgeable, caring
          presence can shape the way a family welcomes their newest member.
        </p>
        <p>
          I believe every mother deserves to feel seen, heard, and supported —
          no matter how their birth unfolds. My role isn't to have a birth go a certain
          way, but to ensure that <em>you</em> feel informed, empowered, and at peace with
          your choices every step of the way.
        </p>
        <p>
          Whether you're planning a medicated hospital birth, an unmedicated birth center
          experience, or anything in between, I show up for you without judgment and with
          my whole heart.
        </p>

        <h2>Training &amp; Credentials</h2>
        <ul class="credentials">
          <li>Certified Birth Doula — DONA International</li>
          <li>CPR &amp; First Aid Certified</li>
          <li>Breastfeeding / Chestfeeding Support Training</li>
          <li>Ongoing continuing education in perinatal support</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>My Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          I believe in the innate strength and wisdom of a mother's body. My support
          centers the needs and desires of each unique family. I bring evidence-based
          information, a calm steady presence, and a deep respect for your autonomy
          to every birth.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of doula work, I'm a mother, a reader, an avid tea drinker, and a
          firm believer that it truly takes a village to raise a child — and to birth one.
        </p>

